768
00:46:32,110 --> 00:46:35,460
When I was a boy, my father, Avatar Aang,

769
00:46:35,460 --> 00:46:40,200
told me the story of how he and his friends
heroically ended the Hundred Year War.

770
00:46:41,260 --> 00:46:44,820
Avatar Aang and Fire Lord
Zuko transformed the Fire

771
00:46:44,820 --> 00:46:48,230
Nation colonies into the
United Republic of Nations,

772
00:46:48,230 --> 00:46:52,940
a society where benders and
non-benders from all over the world,

773
00:46:52,940 --> 00:46:56,570
could live and thrive together
in peace and harmony.

774
00:46:57,460 --> 00:47:00,960
They named the capital of this
great land, Republic City.

775
00:47:03,150 --> 00:47:06,840
Avatar Aang accomplished many
remarkable things in his life.

776
00:47:07,360 --> 00:47:10,530
But sadly, his time in
this world came to an end.

777
00:47:10,970 --> 00:47:15,780
And like the cycle of the seasons,
the cycle of the Avatar, began anew.

778
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:42,330
The White Lotus has honored my
family by coming. Thank you.

779
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:47,020
Welcome.

780
00:47:49,230 --> 00:47:53,950
We have investigated many claims,
both here and in the Northern Tribe.

781
00:47:54,060 --> 00:47:55,600
All have turned out to be false.

782
00:47:56,990 --> 00:48:00,160
Then you should be happy to know,
your search has come to an end.

783
00:48:00,530 --> 00:48:03,680
What makes you so sure
your daughter is the one?

784
00:48:04,420 --> 00:48:06,520
Korra! Please come in here!

785
00:48:09,530 --> 00:48:12,740
I'm the Avatar! You gotta deal with it!

786
00:48:56,840 --> 00:48:58,100
She's strong.

787
00:48:58,580 --> 00:49:00,340
She lacks restraint.

788
00:49:22,430 --> 00:49:25,210
Hey, why all the doom and gloom, people?

789
00:49:25,280 --> 00:49:28,840
We should be celebrating!
Three elements down, one to go!

790
00:49:29,170 --> 00:49:31,620
You're getting ahead of
yourself as usual, Korra.

791
00:49:31,760 --> 00:49:34,400
We haven't decided if you passed
your firebending test yet.

792
00:49:34,430 --> 00:49:38,100
Ever since you were a little girl, you've
excelled at the physical side of bending,

793
00:49:38,100 --> 00:49:43,380
but completely ignored the spiritual side.
The Avatar must master both.

794
00:49:43,880 --> 00:49:46,620
I haven't ignored it, it just
doesn't come as easy to me.

795
00:49:46,970 --> 00:49:51,640
But that's why I should start training with
Tenzin immediately. He's Mister Spiritual.

796
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:54,210
Do you think she's ready, Master Katara?

797
00:49:54,480 --> 00:49:59,350
Yes. If anyone can teach her what
she needs to learn, it's Tenzin.

798
00:49:59,810 --> 00:50:04,080
Very well, Korra. It's time for you
to begin your airbending training.

799
00:50:04,300 --> 00:50:06,160
Yes! Finally!

800
00:50:08,520 --> 00:50:12,870
I mean, thank you all for believing in me.

801
00:50:20,220 --> 00:50:21,850
Naga, you should have seen it!

802
00:50:22,730 --> 00:50:25,160
I kicked some firebender
butt, and I passed!

803
00:50:26,190 --> 00:50:27,810
Tenzin will be here in a few days.

804
00:50:36,180 --> 00:50:38,200
Just taking Naga out for a stroll.

805
00:50:40,490 --> 00:50:42,500
Don't worry, we're not going far.

806
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:56,080
Naga, go!

807
00:50:57,060 --> 00:50:58,670
Better girl. Go! Go! Go!

808
00:51:08,690 --> 00:51:11,410
Are we there yet? Are we there yet?
Are we there yet? It looks like we're there.

809
00:51:11,410 --> 00:51:14,000
I know it, this is very familiar!
Are we here yet? Are we here yet?

810
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:15,010
Ooh, please tell me we're here!

811
00:51:15,020 --> 00:51:19,110
Yes, Ikki, as I've been telling
you for the last fifteen minutes,

812
00:51:19,110 --> 00:51:22,130
we are, finally, here.

813
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:25,620
Hello, mother.

814
00:51:26,150 --> 00:51:30,450
I can't tell you how happy I am to see you.
Please, help me.

815
00:51:32,020 --> 00:51:33,810
Unhand me, strange woman!

816
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,560
That's your grandmother, Meelo.

817
00:51:39,550 --> 00:51:42,100
It's so good to see all of you.

818
00:51:42,390 --> 00:51:45,680
Gran Gran, I've been reading
all about your old adventures.

819
00:51:45,690 --> 00:51:48,910
I've been dying to ask you,
what happened to Zuko's mom?

820
00:51:49,150 --> 00:51:51,810
Well, Jinora, it's an incredible tale!

821
00:51:51,920 --> 00:51:56,500
Gran Gran, you look old. How old are you?
And why is it so cold in the South Pole?

822
00:51:56,500 --> 00:51:58,460
Can we make a campfire,
and all hurdle around it,

823
00:51:58,460 --> 00:52:00,220
and tell scary stories, and make snowmen?

824
00:52:00,220 --> 00:52:03,070
And then can you make the snowmen
move with waterbending and chase us?

825
00:52:03,070 --> 00:52:05,310
Wouldn't that be fuuun? Huh? Wouldn't it?

826
00:52:06,070 --> 00:52:09,050
Pema, let me help you.
Careful now, careful.

827
00:52:09,210 --> 00:52:13,170
Stop doting on me.
I'm not helpless, I'm just pregnant.

828
00:52:16,320 --> 00:52:21,170
The baby's strong.
I see another airbender in your future.

829
00:52:21,940 --> 00:52:26,300
All I want is one child
like me, a nice non-bender,

830
00:52:26,300 --> 00:52:28,960
who doesn't blast wind in
my face every five seconds.

831
00:52:29,200 --> 00:52:32,340
Mommy, look, I am a snowbender!

832
00:52:34,960 --> 00:52:38,310
Were Tenzin and his siblings
this crazy when they were kids?

833
00:52:38,620 --> 00:52:44,090
Kya and Bumi certainly were, but Tenzin
is always been... rather serious.

834
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:45,930
Mother, please.

835
00:52:49,020 --> 00:52:55,660
Korra? Look at you, so big and strong.
You've grown into quite the young Avatar.

836
00:52:55,700 --> 00:52:59,910
Master Tenzin, I'm so glad you're
here, I can't wait to get started.

837
00:53:00,210 --> 00:53:01,880
Yes, well...

838
00:53:02,990 --> 00:53:05,430
You're going to have to
tell her sooner or later.

839
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:06,410
Tell me what?

840
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:08,770
You're not staying, are you?

841
00:53:10,440 --> 00:53:16,250
I'm afraid not. We're only visiting for the night.
Then I have to return to Republic City.

842
00:53:16,320 --> 00:53:21,240
But, you're supposed to move here.
You're supposed to teach me.

843
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:25,510
I'm sorry, Korra. Your airbending
training is going to have to wait.

844
00:53:29,390 --> 00:53:33,970
So, how long until you're ready to
teach me airbending? A week? A month?

845
00:53:34,240 --> 00:53:36,060
It could be much longer.

846
00:53:36,340 --> 00:53:39,020
I don't understand.
Why are you making me wait?

847
00:53:39,200 --> 00:53:41,390
I have a responsibility to Republic City.

848
00:53:41,820 --> 00:53:45,710
I am one of its leaders, and the situation
there is very unstable right now.

849
00:53:45,830 --> 00:53:48,940
But you also have a
responsibility to teach me.

850
00:53:49,420 --> 00:53:53,660
Believe me, I'd be happy to find another
airbending master, but you're the only one.

851
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:55,450
We're stuck with each other.

852
00:53:55,730 --> 00:53:57,210
I wish there were another way.

853
00:53:57,340 --> 00:54:02,600
Wait, there is! If you can't stay here, then
I'll go back to Republic City with you!

854
00:54:03,110 --> 00:54:03,870
It's perfect!

855
00:54:04,440 --> 00:54:07,600
Absolutely not!
The city is far too dangerous.

856
00:54:07,850 --> 00:54:12,590
Avatar Aang tasked us with keeping you
safe while you mastered the four elements.

857
00:54:12,790 --> 00:54:15,460
I get that, but I don't think
keeping me locked up in

858
00:54:15,470 --> 00:54:18,080
this compound like a prisoner
is what he had in mind.

859
00:54:18,310 --> 00:54:20,420
I know this is difficult to accept,

860
00:54:20,420 --> 00:54:22,880
but it's not the right time
for you to come to the city.

861
00:54:22,980 --> 00:54:23,560
Whatever.

862
00:54:29,430 --> 00:54:30,580
Goodbye, Gran Gran!

863
00:54:31,190 --> 00:54:32,610
Oogi, yip-yip!

864
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:05,660
Nice night for an escape, isn't it?

865
00:55:07,660 --> 00:55:11,580
I have to leave.
I have to find my own path as the Avatar.

866
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:14,200
I know you do.

867
00:55:16,180 --> 00:55:21,790
Aang's time has passed.
My brother, and many of my friends are gone.

868
00:55:22,390 --> 00:55:25,530
It's time for you, and your
generation to take over the

869
00:55:25,530 --> 00:55:29,620
responsibility of keeping peace,
and balance in the world.

870
00:55:30,530 --> 00:55:33,310
And I think you're going
to be a great Avatar.

871
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:34,710
Thank you.

872
00:55:36,060 --> 00:55:37,420
Goodbye, Korra.

873
00:55:50,220 --> 00:55:51,550
Mom, dad...,

874
00:55:53,300 --> 00:55:53,930
I'll miss you.

875
00:55:54,970 --> 00:55:56,760
We love you so much.

876
00:56:33,190 --> 00:56:34,080
Naga, we're here!

877
00:56:45,100 --> 00:56:46,040
Thanks for the ride!

878
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:57,510
Wow, look at this place.

879
00:56:58,390 --> 00:57:00,650
I've never seen so many Satomobiles!

880
00:57:11,680 --> 00:57:14,590
Air Temple Island.
That's where Tenzin lives.

881
00:57:15,060 --> 00:57:16,430
You ready for a little swim, girl?

882
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:22,100
Okay, okay! Food first, then air temple!

883
00:57:23,840 --> 00:57:25,650
Watch out, Naga! Look out!

884
00:57:29,410 --> 00:57:30,260
Watch where you're going!

885
00:57:30,260 --> 00:57:33,160
Whoops, sorry about that.
Excuse us. Coming through.

886
00:57:33,160 --> 00:57:35,470
Heads up. Eh, sorry, we're new in town.

887
00:57:43,920 --> 00:57:44,890
Naga, wait.

888
00:57:48,610 --> 00:57:50,260
We'll take one of everything, please.

889
00:57:50,490 --> 00:57:51,900
That will be twenty yuans.

890
00:57:52,070 --> 00:57:55,220
Uh... I don't have any money?

891
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:56,690
Then what good are you to me?

892
00:57:59,830 --> 00:58:02,220
Don't worry, girl. The city's huge.

893
00:58:02,220 --> 00:58:04,710
I bet we could find a place to
rustle up something to eat.

894
00:58:20,740 --> 00:58:24,610
Uh, say, think I can I get one
of them tasty-smelling fishies?

895
00:58:24,690 --> 00:58:27,370
Oh, uh, yeah, sure.

896
00:58:30,680 --> 00:58:34,570
So, do you... live in that bush?

897
00:58:34,770 --> 00:58:37,470
Yes, presently that is what I do call home.

898
00:58:37,880 --> 00:58:40,870
Took me a while to procure
a bush that beauteous.

899
00:58:41,420 --> 00:58:44,140
This park is quite popular
with all the vagabonds.

900
00:58:44,210 --> 00:58:49,830
So there are a lot of you out here?
I thought everyone in this city was "living it up".

901
00:58:51,700 --> 00:58:55,620
Hey, you've got a lot to learn newcomer.
Welcome to Republic City.

902
00:58:56,920 --> 00:58:57,910
Hey you!

903
00:58:57,920 --> 00:59:00,050
Stop! You can't fish here!

904
00:59:01,310 --> 00:59:02,190
You best skedaddle!

905
00:59:13,710 --> 00:59:19,460
Are you tired of living under the tyranny of benders!
Then join the Equalists!

906
00:59:19,470 --> 00:59:22,840
For too long the bending
elite of this city have

907
00:59:22,840 --> 00:59:26,590
forced non-benders to live
as lower class citizens.

908
00:59:26,590 --> 00:59:31,370
Join Amon, and together we will tear
down the bending establishment.

909
00:59:31,410 --> 00:59:34,650
What are you talking about?
Bending is the coolest thing in the world.

910
00:59:34,780 --> 00:59:38,470
Oh yeah? Let me guess: You're a bender.

911
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:39,730
Yeah, I am.

912
00:59:39,930 --> 00:59:44,660
Then I bet you'd just love to knock me off
this platform with some waterbending, huh?

913
00:59:44,840 --> 00:59:46,490
I'm seriously thinking about it.

914
00:59:47,060 --> 00:59:49,400
This is what's wrong with this city!

915
00:59:49,400 --> 00:59:53,120
Benders like this girl only use
their power to oppress us!

916
00:59:53,950 --> 00:59:55,330
Yeah! Get out of here!

917
00:59:55,370 --> 01:00:00,950
What? I'm not oppressing anyone! You're...
you're oppressing yourselves!

918
01:00:01,070 --> 01:00:03,210
That didn't even make sense.

919
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:11,480
Excuse me, I think I'm lost.

920
01:00:11,690 --> 01:00:13,680
How do I get to Air
Temple Island from here?

921
01:00:13,840 --> 01:00:15,840
Just head down this street.

922
01:00:17,610 --> 01:00:20,340
You should get moving, young lady.
It isn't safe.

923
01:00:24,340 --> 01:00:28,340
Mr. Chung, please tell me
that you have my money,

924
01:00:28,340 --> 01:00:32,430
or else I can't guarantee I can
protect your fine establishment.

925
01:00:32,500 --> 01:00:37,030
I'm sorry, business has been slow.
Please, take one of my phonographs.

926
01:00:39,580 --> 01:00:45,180
My friend here is not a music lover.
Give me the money, or else...

927
01:00:45,190 --> 01:00:46,990
Or else what, hoodlum?

928
01:00:56,250 --> 01:01:01,100
Since you're obviously fresh off the
boat, let me explain a couple things.

929
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:07,450
You're in Triple Threat Triad territory, and
we're about to put you, in the hospital.

930
01:01:07,610 --> 01:01:10,050
You're the only ones who
are gonna need a hospital,

931
01:01:10,050 --> 01:01:12,810
and, for your sake, I
hope there's one nearby.

932
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:14,500
Who do you think you are?

933
01:01:14,650 --> 01:01:16,510
Why don't you come and find out?

934
01:01:28,900 --> 01:01:29,800
What just happened?

935
01:01:29,800 --> 01:01:31,120
Did she just earthbend?

936
01:01:42,030 --> 01:01:43,370
Can she firebend too?

937
01:01:43,370 --> 01:01:44,820
Could she be...

938
01:01:51,050 --> 01:01:54,120
Got an idea about who I am now, chumps?

939
01:01:58,780 --> 01:01:59,100
Come on!

940
01:02:02,010 --> 01:02:03,400
You're not getting away!

941
01:02:17,510 --> 01:02:19,860
Police! Freeze where you are!

942
01:02:26,140 --> 01:02:27,930
Cool! Metalbenders!

943
01:02:35,410 --> 01:02:37,630
I caught the bad guys for you, officers.

944
01:02:38,380 --> 01:02:39,120
Arrest them!

945
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:46,140
You're under arrest, too.

946
01:02:50,050 --> 01:02:51,730
What do you mean I'm under arrest?

947
01:02:51,950 --> 01:02:54,950
Those are the bad guys over there!
They were smashing up the shop!

948
01:02:55,140 --> 01:02:57,860
From the looks of it, you smashed
up a lot more than that.

949
01:02:58,910 --> 01:03:01,340
Wait, you can't arrest me! Let me explain!

950
01:03:01,500 --> 01:03:04,830
You can explain all you
like, down at headquarters.

951
01:04:15,920 --> 01:04:16,690
Let's see.

952
01:04:17,340 --> 01:04:22,040
Multiple counts of destruction
of private and city property,

953
01:04:22,050 --> 01:04:24,570
not to mention evading arrest...

954
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:27,490
You're in a whole mess
of trouble, young lady.

955
01:04:27,550 --> 01:04:30,220
But there were some thugs threatening a
helpless shopkeeper, and I had it...

956
01:04:30,220 --> 01:04:34,040
Can it! You should have called the
police and stayed out of the way.

957
01:04:34,190 --> 01:04:38,200
But I couldn't just sit by and do nothing.
It's my duty to help people.

958
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:40,820
See, I'm the Avatar.

959
01:04:40,990 --> 01:04:43,700
Oh, I am well aware of who you are.

960
01:04:43,700 --> 01:04:48,430
And your Avatar title might
impress some people, but not me.

961
01:04:49,260 --> 01:04:52,970
All right, fine. Then I want to
talk to whoever's in charge.

962
01:04:53,090 --> 01:04:56,120
You're talking to her. I am Chief Beifong.

963
01:04:56,580 --> 01:05:00,890
Wait, Beifong? Lin Beifong?
You're Toph's daughter!

964
01:05:01,030 --> 01:05:01,700
What of it?

965
01:05:01,940 --> 01:05:04,080
Well then, why are you
treating me like a criminal?

966
01:05:04,460 --> 01:05:08,020
Avatar Aang and your mother were friends.
They saved the world together.

967
01:05:08,230 --> 01:05:09,520
That's ancient history.

968
01:05:09,810 --> 01:05:12,980
And it's got diddly-squat to do
with the mess you're in right now.

969
01:05:13,190 --> 01:05:17,780
You can't just waltz in here and doll out
vigilante justice like you own the place.

970
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:21,250
Chief, Councilman Tenzin is here.

971
01:05:22,460 --> 01:05:23,200
Let him in.

972
01:05:27,000 --> 01:05:28,950
Tenzin, sorry...

973
01:05:29,510 --> 01:05:31,910
I got a little sidetracked
on my way to see you.

974
01:05:35,520 --> 01:05:37,830
Lin, you are looking radiant as usual.

975
01:05:37,880 --> 01:05:41,530
Cut the garbage, Tenzin.
Why is the Avatar in Republic City?

976
01:05:41,650 --> 01:05:45,020
I thought you were supposed to be moving
down to the South Pole to train her.

977
01:05:45,080 --> 01:05:47,330
My relocation has been delayed.

978
01:05:47,580 --> 01:05:50,970
The Avatar on the other hand
will be heading back to

979
01:05:50,970 --> 01:05:54,380
the South Pole immediately,
where she will stay put.

980
01:05:54,610 --> 01:05:54,840
But...

981
01:05:54,850 --> 01:05:59,250
If you would be so kind as to
drop the charges against Korra,

982
01:05:59,250 --> 01:06:05,050
I will take full responsibility for today's
regrettable events and cover all the damages.

983
01:06:08,130 --> 01:06:10,920
Fine. Get her out of my city.

984
01:06:11,180 --> 01:06:14,090
Always a pleasure, Lin. Let's go, Korra.

985
01:06:24,150 --> 01:06:26,470
Tenzin, please, don't send me back home.

986
01:06:26,590 --> 01:06:30,350
You blatantly disobeyed my wishes
and the orders of the White Lotus.

987
01:06:30,580 --> 01:06:35,260
Katara agreed with me that I should come!
She said my destiny is in Republic City.

988
01:06:35,440 --> 01:06:37,180
Don't bring my mother into this!

989
01:06:37,440 --> 01:06:40,680
Look, I can't wait any longer
to finish my training.

990
01:06:40,680 --> 01:06:44,650
Being cooped up and hidden away from the world
isn't helping me become a better Avatar.

991
01:06:45,120 --> 01:06:49,040
I saw a lot of the city today,
and it's totally out of whack.

992
01:06:49,640 --> 01:06:55,200
I understand now why you need to stay.
Republic City does need you. But it needs me, too.

993
01:06:55,530 --> 01:06:56,020
You...

994
01:06:59,860 --> 01:07:02,350
Is this your polar bear dog, miss?

995
01:07:31,670 --> 01:07:33,500
Korra!

996
01:07:35,230 --> 01:07:37,410
Are you coming to live
with us on the island?

997
01:07:37,750 --> 01:07:41,590
No, I'm sorry, Ikki. I have to go home.

998
01:07:48,630 --> 01:07:49,220
Wait.

999
01:07:50,670 --> 01:07:53,370
I have done my best to guide
Republic City towards the

1000
01:07:53,380 --> 01:07:56,160
dream my father had for
it, but you're right.

1001
01:07:56,310 --> 01:07:58,670
It has fallen out of
balance since he passed.

1002
01:07:58,950 --> 01:08:00,790
I thought I should put off
your training in order

1003
01:08:00,790 --> 01:08:02,250
to uphold his legacy,

1004
01:08:03,040 --> 01:08:05,040
but you are his legacy.

1005
01:08:06,010 --> 01:08:08,480
You may stay and train
airbending here with me.

1006
01:08:08,980 --> 01:08:11,320
Republic City needs its Avatar once again.

1007
01:08:11,490 --> 01:08:14,440
Yes! Thank you! You're the best!

1008
01:08:31,090 --> 01:08:33,280
Hello? I'm Korra,

1009
01:08:34,650 --> 01:08:36,440
I'm Korra, your new Avatar.

1010
01:08:37,150 --> 01:08:38,980
Does this mean you've
moved to Republic City?

1011
01:08:38,980 --> 01:08:41,500
Were you trying to send a message
to the Triads yesterday?

1012
01:08:41,500 --> 01:08:45,180
Will you be fighting crime or the
Anti-bending Revolution, or both?

1013
01:08:45,180 --> 01:08:47,490
Will you be working with Chief
Beifong and the police?

1014
01:08:47,700 --> 01:08:54,750
Uh... yes, I am definitely here to stay, but
honestly I-I don't exactly have a plan yet.

1015
01:08:54,890 --> 01:08:59,150
See, I'm still in training,
but, look, all I know is

1016
01:08:59,150 --> 01:09:04,460
Avatar Aang meant for this city to be the
center of peace and balance in the world,

1017
01:09:04,890 --> 01:09:08,630
and I believe we can
make history a reality.

1018
01:09:09,430 --> 01:09:11,380
I look forward to serving you!

1019
01:09:12,450 --> 01:09:16,290
I'm so happy to be here.
Thank you, Republic City!

1020
01:09:16,380 --> 01:09:18,090
All right, that's all
the questions the Av...

1021
01:09:19,080 --> 01:09:21,570
Amon, how do you wanna handle this?

1022
01:09:22,220 --> 01:09:27,960
So, the Avatar has arrived early.
It looks like we'll have to accelerate our plans.

1023
01:09:46,910 --> 01:09:51,460
And, in the final round, the Buzzard
Wasps won with a decisive knockout!

1024
01:09:51,980 --> 01:09:55,460
What do you say we go to the arena tonight,
catch a few pro-bending matches?

1025
01:09:55,860 --> 01:09:59,310
That sport is a mockery of the
noble tradition of bending.

1026
01:09:59,380 --> 01:10:00,790
Come on Tenzin!

1027
01:10:01,080 --> 01:10:03,250
I've dreamed about seeing a
pro-bending match since I was

1028
01:10:03,250 --> 01:10:05,750
a kid and now I'm just a ferry
ride away from the arena.

1029
01:10:05,750 --> 01:10:10,100
Korra, you're not here to watch that drivel.
You're here to finish your Avatar training.

1030
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:13,270
So for the time being I want
you to remain on the island.

1031
01:10:13,370 --> 01:10:16,520
Is that why you're keeping the White Lotus
sentries around to watch my every move?

1032
01:10:16,620 --> 01:10:17,190
Yes.

1033
01:10:17,710 --> 01:10:20,790
In order to learn airbending I
believe you require a calm,

1034
01:10:20,790 --> 01:10:23,740
quiet environment - free
from any distractions.

1035
01:10:24,120 --> 01:10:25,870
All right, you're the master.

1036
01:10:34,580 --> 01:10:38,650
So, my mother informed me that you've
never been able to airbend before.

1037
01:10:40,620 --> 01:10:44,180
Yeah, but I don't know why.
The other elements came so easily to me.

1038
01:10:44,180 --> 01:10:48,400
But every single time I've
tried airbending; Nothing.

1039
01:10:48,810 --> 01:10:51,170
That's perfectly alright.
You just need to be patient.

1040
01:10:51,580 --> 01:10:54,140
Often the element that's most
difficult for the Avatar to

1041
01:10:54,140 --> 01:10:57,370
master is the one most opposite
to the Avatar's personality.

1042
01:10:57,730 --> 01:10:59,220
For Aang it was earthbending.

1043
01:10:59,430 --> 01:11:02,380
Well I'm about as opposite
an airbender as you can get.

1044
01:11:03,070 --> 01:11:04,910
Let's begin your first lesson.

1045
01:11:07,930 --> 01:11:10,570
Korra's gonna' airbend!
Korra's gonna' airbend!

1046
01:11:10,570 --> 01:11:12,110
What on earth is that contraption?

1047
01:11:12,360 --> 01:11:16,980
A time honored tool that teaches the
most fundamental aspect of airbending.

1048
01:11:17,190 --> 01:11:19,460
Jinora, would you like to
explain this exercise?

1049
01:11:19,810 --> 01:11:22,040
The goal is to weave your
way through the gates and

1050
01:11:22,040 --> 01:11:24,130
make it to the other side
without touching them.

1051
01:11:24,850 --> 01:11:25,990
Seems easy enough.

1052
01:11:26,230 --> 01:11:29,060
Jinora forgot to say that you have to get
through while the gates are spinning.

1053
01:11:38,720 --> 01:11:41,520
The key is to be like the leaf.

1054
01:11:43,350 --> 01:11:46,550
Flow - with the movement of the gates.

1055
01:11:48,400 --> 01:11:49,710
Jinora will demonstrate.

1056
01:11:52,080 --> 01:11:54,670
Airbending is all about spiral movements.

1057
01:11:55,110 --> 01:11:59,220
When you meet resistance, you must be able
to switch direction at a moment's notice.

1058
01:12:06,870 --> 01:12:08,050
Let's do this!

1059
01:12:24,880 --> 01:12:26,550
Don't force your way through!

1060
01:12:27,590 --> 01:12:29,480
Dance! Dance like the wind!

1061
01:12:30,130 --> 01:12:31,480
Be the leaf...

1062
01:12:43,930 --> 01:12:44,650
Airbend!

1063
01:12:48,070 --> 01:12:51,150
What is wrong with me? Airbend!

1064
01:12:58,080 --> 01:13:00,590
Maybe I'm just not cut out to
be an airbender, huh Naga?

1065
01:13:00,840 --> 01:13:01,620
Ladies and gentlemen!

1066
01:13:01,620 --> 01:13:06,680
I'm coming to you live from Republic City's
pro-bending arena - where tonight the best

1067
01:13:06,680 --> 01:13:11,040
in the world continue their quest for a spot
in the upcoming championship tournament.

1068
01:13:11,350 --> 01:13:16,160
Grab your snacks and grab your kids because
this next match is gonna' be a doozie!

1069
01:13:17,030 --> 01:13:20,560
This Mako's got moxy!
He advances, fires two quick shots.

1070
01:13:20,560 --> 01:13:24,890
Yomo is hammered back to zone three!
The clock is winding down, can Yomo hold on?

1071
01:13:25,120 --> 01:13:28,650
He's teetering on the edge of the ring now.
The Fire Ferrets line up to strike!

1072
01:13:32,210 --> 01:13:33,520
Korra, come down here please!

1073
01:13:36,470 --> 01:13:38,120
You shut it off at the best part!

1074
01:13:38,280 --> 01:13:43,490
I thought I made myself clear.
I don't want you listening to this distracting nonsense.

1075
01:13:43,490 --> 01:13:44,910
But it's their radio.

1076
01:13:44,910 --> 01:13:47,750
And technically you said I
couldn't watch a match,

1077
01:13:47,750 --> 01:13:49,780
you didn't say anything
about listening to one.

1078
01:13:49,780 --> 01:13:52,680
You... You know what I meant!

1079
01:13:53,050 --> 01:13:55,700
Anyway shouldn't y- Shouldn't
you be in bed by now!

1080
01:14:14,680 --> 01:14:15,880
I think I'm doing it wrong.

1081
01:14:16,300 --> 01:14:17,450
There's nothing to do.

1082
01:14:17,910 --> 01:14:22,030
Let your mind and your spirit be free,
for air is the element of freedom.

1083
01:14:24,960 --> 01:14:26,500
Is something funny?

1084
01:14:26,500 --> 01:14:30,820
Yeah, you're telling me to embrace freedom but
you won't even let me listen to the radio.

1085
01:14:31,210 --> 01:14:33,280
And forget about leaving this island!

1086
01:14:33,520 --> 01:14:34,370
Please, Korra.

1087
01:14:34,990 --> 01:14:37,950
Look at Meelo, he's able
to meditate peacefully.

1088
01:14:41,380 --> 01:14:43,130
Actually, I think he's asleep.

1089
01:14:43,250 --> 01:14:46,750
What?! Well, at least he has
the relaxing part down.

1090
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:50,120
Whatever. None of this airbending
stuff makes any sense to me.

1091
01:14:50,390 --> 01:14:53,890
I know you're frustrated, but these
teachings will sink in over time.

1092
01:14:54,220 --> 01:14:56,720
Then one day, they'll just click.

1093
01:15:00,360 --> 01:15:04,060
Yeah, it's not sinking in yet.
I'm gonna get a glass of lychee juice.

1094
01:15:04,210 --> 01:15:06,120
Korra, the meditation's not over yet!

1095
01:15:07,100 --> 01:15:09,130
Daddy, can I have some lychee juice too?

1096
01:15:09,130 --> 01:15:09,490
No.

1097
01:16:18,490 --> 01:16:20,850
Hey, what're you doin' in my gym?

1098
01:16:21,170 --> 01:16:23,890
Uh, I was just looking for a
bathroom when I got lost.

1099
01:16:23,890 --> 01:16:26,830
Ah, the old "I had to pee" excuse!

1100
01:16:26,830 --> 01:16:29,850
You know, I'm sick and tired of you
kids sneakin' in without payin'!

1101
01:16:29,850 --> 01:16:31,370
I'm taking you to security!

1102
01:16:31,370 --> 01:16:32,280
No, wait!

1103
01:16:32,280 --> 01:16:35,340
There you are!
I've been looking everywhere for you!

1104
01:16:35,820 --> 01:16:38,350
It's all right Toza, she's with me.

1105
01:16:38,350 --> 01:16:39,320
Yeah, I'm with him.

1106
01:16:39,320 --> 01:16:41,090
So, you see, we're together.

1107
01:16:41,090 --> 01:16:43,350
Well, not together together,
more like friends.

1108
01:16:43,350 --> 01:16:45,500
Right, friends.
No, no, I didn't mean to imply.

1109
01:16:45,500 --> 01:16:46,380
Oh, you implied it.

1110
01:16:46,630 --> 01:16:49,430
Ah, I don't care what you are!
I got work to do.

1111
01:16:51,200 --> 01:16:53,620
Ooh, right this way, miss.

1112
01:16:53,930 --> 01:16:55,020
Ah, thank you sir!

1113
01:16:56,000 --> 01:16:56,970
Seriously, thanks.

1114
01:17:00,270 --> 01:17:03,120
Whaddya think?
Best seats in the house, huh?

1115
01:17:03,580 --> 01:17:06,750
Wow! Unbelievable!

1116
01:17:07,400 --> 01:17:10,200
This place is even more
amazing than I imagined!

1117
01:17:10,320 --> 01:17:11,740
Name's Bolin, by the way.

1118
01:17:11,740 --> 01:17:12,420
Korra.

1119
01:17:14,160 --> 01:17:14,780
Bolin.

1120
01:17:15,530 --> 01:17:15,930
Yeah.

1121
01:17:16,150 --> 01:17:20,700
I told you. You have to stop bringing your
crazy fangirls in here before the matches.

1122
01:17:20,960 --> 01:17:21,980
Get her out of here.

1123
01:17:22,230 --> 01:17:24,480
Come on, Mako!

1124
01:17:24,970 --> 01:17:27,580
Right, look, I kinda
promised her she could stay,

1125
01:17:27,580 --> 01:17:30,610
but man, I got a good feeling,
there's somethin' special about her.

1126
01:17:30,870 --> 01:17:31,630
I know it!

1127
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:34,600
Come here, I want you to
meet my brother, Mako.

1128
01:17:34,980 --> 01:17:38,280
Mako? Wow, I- I heard you
playing on the radio.

1129
01:17:38,280 --> 01:17:39,550
Come on, Bolin, we're up.

1130
01:17:40,320 --> 01:17:42,350
Or I could meet him later.

1131
01:17:42,350 --> 01:17:46,580
Yeah, sorry about that.
My brother just gets real focused before a match.

1132
01:17:47,170 --> 01:17:49,780
Okay, I gotta go, wish me luck.

1133
01:17:50,010 --> 01:17:51,650
Not... that I'll need it.

1134
01:17:53,170 --> 01:17:55,060
Good luck. Knock 'em out!

1135
01:18:00,820 --> 01:18:05,480
Introducing the Fire Ferrets!

1136
01:18:06,380 --> 01:18:08,130
I love you Bolin.

1137
01:18:08,500 --> 01:18:10,880
The rookie Ferrets came from
out of nowhere and have

1138
01:18:10,880 --> 01:18:13,380
made it further than anyone
expected this season.

1139
01:18:13,390 --> 01:18:16,340
But tonight they face their
toughest test yet folks.

1140
01:18:19,540 --> 01:18:24,280
And they’re off. The two teams waste no time
trying to blast each other out of zone 1.

1141
01:18:27,150 --> 01:18:29,570
Hasook is the first to feel
the heat of the Tigerdilloes,

1142
01:18:30,150 --> 01:18:32,780
he tries to return the favor
but they’re too fast for him.

1143
01:18:33,220 --> 01:18:36,410
While Mako showcases his
trademark cool under fire style.

1144
01:18:39,490 --> 01:18:43,180
The Tigerdilloes score with
a walloping one-two combo.

1145
01:18:44,040 --> 01:18:47,130
Can the teammate hold on
to their zone 1 territory...

1146
01:18:50,770 --> 01:18:53,080
guess not. Mako’s over the line.

1147
01:18:53,290 --> 01:18:56,320
The Tigerdilloes get the green line
and advance into Ferret territory.

1148
01:18:56,550 --> 01:18:57,940
Come on Ferrets!

1149
01:19:01,420 --> 01:19:05,320
Look’s like Hasook’s in trouble.
He’s in zone 3 teetering over the drink.

1150
01:19:08,470 --> 01:19:11,800
And Hasook takes a dip.
He’ll be back for round two.

1151
01:19:11,800 --> 01:19:14,990
Assuming the fabulous bending brothers can
hold their ground until he next round.

1152
01:19:17,770 --> 01:19:23,730
Round 1 goes to the Golden
Temple Tigerdilloes!

1153
01:19:23,910 --> 01:19:25,790
Come on Hasook get your act together!

1154
01:19:30,280 --> 01:19:34,490
The Fire Ferrets are knocked into
zone 2 and the Tigerdilloes advance.

1155
01:19:51,490 --> 01:19:55,610
The Fire Ferrets sinch the round in the
closing seconds. That’s one a piece.

1156
01:19:55,920 --> 01:19:59,250
Still anyone’s match as we go
into the third and final round.

1157
01:20:01,800 --> 01:20:05,800
Hasook stumbles and now he
tumbles right into his teammate.

1158
01:20:05,800 --> 01:20:10,190
He and Bolin better untangle quick
if they don’t want to—Oh too late!

1159
01:20:11,180 --> 01:20:12,060
Oh no!

1160
01:20:12,430 --> 01:20:15,640
It’s all up to Mako now,
he’s bobbing and weaving,

1161
01:20:15,640 --> 01:20:18,640
he’s weaving and bobbing
but he’s not hitting back!

1162
01:20:18,640 --> 01:20:21,940
If Mako’s knocked out the
Ferrets’ fabulous season is over.

1163
01:20:23,450 --> 01:20:27,240
He is dancing on the edge of the ring
surviving the three on one barrage.

1164
01:20:27,470 --> 01:20:30,580
It seems his plan is to let the
Tigerdilloes punch themselves out.

1165
01:20:30,720 --> 01:20:33,840
And his plan is working.
Han is in the pool!

1166
01:20:33,840 --> 01:20:37,430
They’ve got nothing left in the
tank and Mako is on the offensive!

1167
01:20:38,830 --> 01:20:44,500
It’s two on one, scratch that it’s one on one.
And it’s an Earth and Fire slugfest!

1168
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:49,650
There’s so much smoke and dust from the fire
and I can’t even see where the Fire Ferret is.

1169
01:20:53,940 --> 01:20:55,350
It's a knock-out!

1170
01:20:55,350 --> 01:20:57,740
What a win they had a hat trick folks!

1171
01:20:57,840 --> 01:21:01,890
Mako pulls off the upset of the season
winning the match for the Fire Ferrets!

1172
01:21:10,600 --> 01:21:15,690
Woohoo! Yes! One more win and we’re
in the championship tournament!

1173
01:21:17,190 --> 01:21:21,510
So, what’d ya think Korra?
Bolin’s got some moves huh?

1174
01:21:21,720 --> 01:21:25,940
What did I think? What did I think?
That was amazing!

1175
01:21:25,940 --> 01:21:29,720
You did more harm than good out there.
You almost cost us the match.

1176
01:21:29,720 --> 01:21:30,860
We won didn’t we?

1177
01:21:30,860 --> 01:21:31,520
Barely.

1178
01:21:31,530 --> 01:21:32,810
Get off my case pal.

1179
01:21:34,750 --> 01:21:35,590
Useless.

1180
01:21:35,810 --> 01:21:40,350
You guys were incredible out there.
Especially you Mr. Hatrick.

1181
01:21:40,600 --> 01:21:41,880
Oh you’re still here…

1182
01:21:41,880 --> 01:21:43,190
Oh you’re still a jerk….anyway,

1183
01:21:45,240 --> 01:21:50,140
Anyway, I’ve been immersed in bending my whole
life but I never learned to move like that.

1184
01:21:50,140 --> 01:21:54,150
It’s like there’s a whole new style here.
Think you could show me a few tricks?

1185
01:21:54,360 --> 01:21:56,210
Absolutely!

1186
01:21:56,490 --> 01:21:58,940
Right now? Come on Bolin.

1187
01:21:59,360 --> 01:22:02,530
Just ignore him.
Yeah I could show you the basics.

1188
01:22:02,770 --> 01:22:05,230
I’m just not sure how my
Earthbending would translate

1189
01:22:05,230 --> 01:22:07,810
to your Waterbending but
we’ll figure it out.

1190
01:22:07,810 --> 01:22:10,050
Won’t be a problem, I’m
actually an Earthbender.

1191
01:22:11,100 --> 01:22:14,950
I’m sorry! No, no I didn’t mean to assume...
I was just figuring,

1192
01:22:14,950 --> 01:22:19,270
with your Water Tribe get up
that you are a Water Tribe gal.

1193
01:22:19,900 --> 01:22:23,300
No you’re right.
I’m a Waterbender and a Firebender.

1194
01:22:25,700 --> 01:22:26,880
I’m very confused right now.

1195
01:22:28,040 --> 01:22:30,550
You’re the Avatar and I’m an idiot.

1196
01:22:30,550 --> 01:22:32,210
Both are true.

1197
01:22:33,010 --> 01:22:36,590
No way… The Avatar!

1198
01:22:38,160 --> 01:22:40,060
Alright. Let’s see what you got.

1199
01:22:44,580 --> 01:22:50,190
That was great! Good power!
But in a real match you’d be a sitting turtleduck.

1200
01:22:50,430 --> 01:22:52,020
Not so upright and flatfooted.

1201
01:22:52,020 --> 01:22:54,670
Stay light on your toes
right up until the moment

1202
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:57,370
when you need to dig in and strike.
Then...

1203
01:23:01,580 --> 01:23:03,270
Okay, let me try it again.

1204
01:23:08,040 --> 01:23:12,110
Wow! Nice adjustment.
You’re a natural at this!

1205
01:23:12,110 --> 01:23:12,790
Not bad.

1206
01:23:13,250 --> 01:23:15,120
What’s it take to impress this guy?

1207
01:23:15,260 --> 01:23:17,370
What? I said not bad.

1208
01:23:19,040 --> 01:23:23,400
You know what, it’s getting late.
I think I’m gonna turn in. You kids have fun.

1209
01:23:23,700 --> 01:23:25,800
Nice to meet you Avatar Korra.

1210
01:23:26,790 --> 01:23:28,710
Yeah real pleasure.

1211
01:23:28,710 --> 01:23:30,060
See you upstairs bro.

1212
01:23:30,070 --> 01:23:31,970
Upstairs? You guys live here?

1213
01:23:32,140 --> 01:23:36,340
Yeah, in the attic, it’s nothing fancy but
we have great views. But back to bending.

1214
01:23:36,700 --> 01:23:40,370
So, back to bending. Why don’t you
throw that combination one more time.

1215
01:23:52,180 --> 01:23:53,400
Patience Korra!

1216
01:24:06,590 --> 01:24:13,720
That was a 2000 year old historical
treasure…what…what is wrong with you?!

1217
01:24:13,720 --> 01:24:17,390
There’s nothing wrong with me!
I’ve been practicing just like you taught me!

1218
01:24:17,390 --> 01:24:21,730
But it isn’t sinking in okay!
It hasn’t clicked like you said it would!

1219
01:24:21,730 --> 01:24:25,570
Korra this isn’t something you can force.
If you would only listen to me…

1220
01:24:25,580 --> 01:24:27,650
I have been!
But you know what I think?

1221
01:24:27,650 --> 01:24:29,380
Maybe the problem isn’t me,

1222
01:24:29,380 --> 01:24:33,750
maybe the reason I haven’t learned Airbending
yet is because you’re a terrible teacher.

1223
01:24:36,040 --> 01:24:38,170
Yeah you’re a terrible teacher Daddy!

1224
01:24:52,020 --> 01:24:56,270
Okay! Everyone here? Wait…where’s Korra?

1225
01:24:56,500 --> 01:24:59,130
Honestly Pema, I am at my wit’s
end with that girl. I...

1226
01:24:59,470 --> 01:25:00,870
I don’t know how to get through to her.

1227
01:25:02,890 --> 01:25:07,460
Dear the best thing you can do right
now is give Korra some space.

1228
01:25:08,010 --> 01:25:10,850
You must promise me that your
teenage years won’t be like this.

1229
01:25:12,590 --> 01:25:14,360
I will make no such promises.

1230
01:25:21,430 --> 01:25:24,990
I didn’t miss your match did I?
You guys look like you lost already.

1231
01:25:25,140 --> 01:25:26,410
We might as well have.

1232
01:25:26,410 --> 01:25:28,340
Hasook’s a no good no show.

1233
01:25:29,210 --> 01:25:32,800
You got two minutes to come out ready
to play or you’re disqualified.

1234
01:25:33,340 --> 01:25:37,000
Well there goes our shot at the
tournament and the winnings.

1235
01:25:37,270 --> 01:25:39,000
Couldn’t you ask one of
those guys to fill in?

1236
01:25:39,220 --> 01:25:42,230
Nah, the rules say you can
only compete on one team.

1237
01:25:42,480 --> 01:25:48,080
Well then…how about about me?
I’m a topnotch Waterbender if I do say so myself.

1238
01:25:48,080 --> 01:25:50,970
But you’re the Avatar…isn’t that cheating?

1239
01:25:50,970 --> 01:25:53,210
It isn’t cheating if I
only do Waterbending.

1240
01:25:53,210 --> 01:25:56,550
No way. I’d rather forfeit then
look like a fool out there.

1241
01:25:56,550 --> 01:25:58,870
Wow thanks for the vote of confidence…

1242
01:25:59,700 --> 01:26:00,790
Time’s up you in or out?

1243
01:26:00,790 --> 01:26:01,270
We’re in.

1244
01:26:01,270 --> 01:26:01,670
We are?

1245
01:26:01,670 --> 01:26:02,000
Yes!

1246
01:26:02,320 --> 01:26:03,490
Hey I didn’t agree to this!

1247
01:26:03,490 --> 01:26:04,640
You can thank me later.

1248
01:26:05,410 --> 01:26:06,710
This girl is crazy…

1249
01:26:07,500 --> 01:26:11,610
Look’s like the Fire Ferrets have ferreted
out a last minute replacement Waterbender.

1250
01:26:11,610 --> 01:26:13,340
Let’s see if she’s another
diamond in the rough

1251
01:26:13,340 --> 01:26:15,590
like the brothers from the
school of hard knocks.

1252
01:26:16,490 --> 01:26:20,490
Don’t do anything too fancy or aggressive.
In fact, don’t do anything.

1253
01:26:20,490 --> 01:26:22,580
Just try not to get knocked off the ring.

1254
01:26:22,750 --> 01:26:24,230
You got it captain.

1255
01:26:25,870 --> 01:26:27,460
Players are you ready?

1256
01:26:34,800 --> 01:26:36,900
Whoo! Man overboard!

1257
01:26:37,030 --> 01:26:40,830
Fire Ferret Waterbender
penalty, move back one zone.

1258
01:26:41,120 --> 01:26:42,520
What? Why?

1259
01:26:42,710 --> 01:26:46,650
You’re only allowed to knock players off
the back of the ring, not over the sides.

1260
01:26:46,820 --> 01:26:48,700
Oh…whoops.

1261
01:26:50,710 --> 01:26:53,120
And we’re back in action after that hiccup.

1262
01:26:53,380 --> 01:26:56,220
But I’m not so sure this replacement
player knows what she’s doing.

1263
01:26:57,650 --> 01:27:00,560
Fowl! Over the line!
Move back to zone three.

1264
01:27:00,780 --> 01:27:03,210
Ugh! I’ll show you over the line.

1265
01:27:06,450 --> 01:27:09,410
The Platypus Bears take round 1.

1266
01:27:10,160 --> 01:27:13,230
The Platypus Bears know a green
player when they see one and

1267
01:27:13,230 --> 01:27:16,590
they are focusing the brunt of
their bending on this poor girl.

1268
01:27:20,340 --> 01:27:23,290
What a minute, did that
Waterbender just Earthbend?

1269
01:27:25,870 --> 01:27:27,840
Fowl!...I think.

1270
01:27:30,860 --> 01:27:31,950
Did I see that right?

1271
01:27:32,380 --> 01:27:34,980
Hold on folks we’re just waiting
for the Referee’s official call,

1272
01:27:34,980 --> 01:27:38,090
but... I think this
replacement player could be…

1273
01:27:38,100 --> 01:27:40,770
Pardon me everyone, has anyone
seen Korra this evening.

1274
01:27:41,100 --> 01:27:41,950
She’s not in her room.

1275
01:27:42,040 --> 01:27:47,720
You’ve gotta be kidding me! She’s the Avatar
folks, playing in a Pro-Bending match!

1276
01:27:47,720 --> 01:27:49,230
Can you believe that?

1277
01:27:49,520 --> 01:27:50,620
I’ll get her myself!

1278
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:58,360
The Avatar will be permitted to continue
so long as she solely bends water.

1279
01:28:03,470 --> 01:28:06,160
This girl may be the Avatar but
she’s no Pro-Bender and the

1280
01:28:06,160 --> 01:28:08,550
Platypus Bears are intent on
exploiting that weakness.

1281
01:28:08,910 --> 01:28:12,760
They’re giving her their best and
her best is not enough to stop it.

1282
01:28:13,030 --> 01:28:15,460
Aaaaaannd... she’s in the drink.

1283
01:28:23,470 --> 01:28:28,320
Oh hey Tenzin…I thought you didn’t
like coming to these matches.

1284
01:28:29,220 --> 01:28:32,400
Once again you have flagrantly
disobeyed my orders.

1285
01:28:32,400 --> 01:28:34,670
You were to stay on the island. Let’s go.

1286
01:28:34,940 --> 01:28:37,060
No! I’m kind of in the middle of something.

1287
01:28:37,390 --> 01:28:40,700
I have tried my very best to get
through to you by being gentle

1288
01:28:40,710 --> 01:28:44,410
and patient but clearly the only
thing you respond to is force.

1289
01:28:44,720 --> 01:28:47,400
So I am ordering you to come
back to the temple right now!

1290
01:28:47,410 --> 01:28:51,880
Why? So I can sit around and meditate
about how bad I am at Airbending?

1291
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:55,510
You know I’m beginning to think there’s a
reason I haven’t been able to learn it,

1292
01:28:55,510 --> 01:28:57,610
because maybe I don’t even need!

1293
01:28:57,900 --> 01:29:00,650
What? That is a Ludacris suggestion!

1294
01:29:00,650 --> 01:29:04,190
The Avatar needs to learn
Airbending, it is not optional!

1295
01:29:04,190 --> 01:29:08,000
No, this is what I need to learn!
Modern styles of fighting!

1296
01:29:08,140 --> 01:29:12,660
Being the Avatar isn’t all about fighting Korra!
When will you learn that?

1297
01:29:12,930 --> 01:29:14,410
I have a match to go finish.

1298
01:29:14,980 --> 01:29:21,650
The Platypus Bears win round 2! Round 3!

1299
01:29:26,570 --> 01:29:30,150
The Platypus Bears come out of the gate
and quickly go after the Ferret brothers.

1300
01:29:30,230 --> 01:29:31,680
They’re corralled in the corner,

1301
01:29:31,680 --> 01:29:36,840
wedged in the edge of zone 1 unable to the
Avatar’s rescue and boy does she need it.

1302
01:29:42,710 --> 01:29:46,830
Looks like the Avatar’s Pro-Bending
debut is gonna be cut short

1303
01:29:46,830 --> 01:29:50,580
as she’s pushed back to zone 3 and
the water is calling her name.

1304
01:29:50,830 --> 01:29:52,880
It’s only a matter of time before...

1305
01:29:53,010 --> 01:29:56,480
Hold the phone, stop the presses!
She’s still in the game folks!

1306
01:29:56,480 --> 01:29:58,720
And she’s moving like an
entirely different player!

1307
01:29:58,720 --> 01:30:02,910
Suddenly all of the Platypus Bear
strikes are only striking air.

1308
01:30:04,180 --> 01:30:05,470
How about that…

1309
01:30:07,960 --> 01:30:12,800
The Platypus Bears have no juice left but
Mako and Bolin are still fresh and juicy.

1310
01:30:37,300 --> 01:30:42,880
Knock-out! The Fire Ferrets come from way
behind and steal the win!

1311
01:30:42,880 --> 01:30:44,110
What an upset folks!

1312
01:30:44,110 --> 01:30:48,860
The rookies, Avatar in tow, have nabbed
a place in the championship tournament!

1313
01:30:48,860 --> 01:30:50,620
I cannot believe it!

1314
01:30:53,130 --> 01:30:54,520
Yeah! Yes!

1315
01:30:55,390 --> 01:31:00,050
Korra, what can I say?
You really came alive in that last round.

1316
01:31:00,420 --> 01:31:03,360
The way you dodged their
attacks…you are a natural.

1317
01:31:03,360 --> 01:31:07,930
Thanks but I can’t take all the credit,
someone else taught me those moves.

1318
01:31:16,370 --> 01:31:20,140
I’m really sorry about everything I said.

1319
01:31:20,140 --> 01:31:23,980
I was really frustrated with
myself and I took it out on you.

1320
01:31:24,200 --> 01:31:30,080
I think I owe an apology too. I was trying
to teach you about patience and I lost mine.

1321
01:31:30,540 --> 01:31:31,510
No hard feelings?

1322
01:31:31,830 --> 01:31:35,410
Of course not. By the way you were
really good out there tonight.

1323
01:31:35,970 --> 01:31:37,790
You moved just like an Airbender.

1324
01:31:38,040 --> 01:31:40,210
Wait... you stayed and watched?

1325
01:31:40,400 --> 01:31:44,350
I did. Pro-Bending turned out to be
the perfect teaching tool for you.

1326
01:31:47,720 --> 01:31:50,440
I’ll see you tomorrow for Airbending
practice bright and early!

1327
01:31:51,050 --> 01:31:54,070
And by the way I kinda permanently
joined the Fire Ferrets

1328
01:31:54,070 --> 01:31:56,110
and we’re playing in the
tournament in a couple of weeks!

1329
01:32:16,350 --> 01:32:20,070
